               <head>Judeo-Persian fragment</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85104172">
                  <summary>A fragment of a polemical tract on the prophethood of Moses and the
							Jewish religion (ff. 2r-9v).</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="jpr" otherLangs="he" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="10v" />
                     <title>Fragment of a polemical tract</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="jpr">אגרת פורסד כו אז צי בי שנאסי כו נביאי בוד <locus n="2r" />
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p>Possibly a fragment of a Sefer ha-Mitsṿot (Book of Precepts),
									probably part of the introduction (Meredith-Owens). </p>
                        <p>According to the National Library of Israel's catalogue, it is a
									fragment of a commentary on the Book of Joshua in
									Judeo-Persian.</p>
                        <p>F. 10 followed by f. 1: an exposition on the commandment of
									circumcision beginning in Hebrew: <quote xml:lang="he">ברוך שהוא
										היה והוא יש והוא יהיה</quote>.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
